In rural Hubei Province, outside Wuhan, Jan. 23 was the "critical day" for many villagers to realize the severity of the epidemic. On that day, Wuhan began to close off the city.

Not to be outdone by the overwhelming pressure to prevent the disease, there was only one doctor in the village, and the village doctors could not find the 44 people every day to check their body temperature.

That night, someone in the village wechat group asked the village cadres, "our village has registered personnel from Wuhan? "

Some people question why old people get masks. The doctor explained: "Old Age, easy to get the disease (pneumonia) . "

This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Tang Yucheng, southern weekly reporter

Southern weekend staff writer Xiang Siqi

Editor in chief | Wu Xiaoyu

An outbreak of pneumonia, which led to the closure of many parts of Hubei Province, did not affect people in Rural Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, 400 km away, as usual.

On Lunar New Year's Eve 2020, people in Xiangyang villages busily change new couplets, stick New Year pictures and hang lanterns, and the sound of firecrackers rises and falls as usual before the reunion dinner.

No one wears a mask. "We don't usually sell masks in villages or towns. Of course, we don't have any now, " said Feng Jiang, the village's only doctor, with a wry smile on his face.

The village is about a six-hour drive from Wuhan. Feng Jiang studied medicine with his father, an old Chinese medicine doctor, at an early age. He has been a village doctor here for nearly 30 years.

His cell phone number was taped to the door of the village clinic. In previous years, he can also go home on Lunar New Year's Eve, villagers have something to call him on the line. This year, his 30th year was broken by an epidemic in Wuhan, riding a motorcycle home for lunch and rushing back to work. The day before, more than 20 people had come to see him for his medicine.

From the township to the village, and then to the village groups, the prevention and control of the rural epidemic is imminent. As of 24:00 on January 24, there had been one confirmed case and 76 suspected cases in Xiangyang, including several suspected cases in rural areas, according to southern weekend.

In the early morning of January 26, People's Daily public number again issued an urgent appeal: "Prevent and control the epidemic situation, don't leave out the countryside! "

1
The postponed country "key day"

1

###The postponed country "key day"

In an earlier telephone interview with southern weekend reporters, several Wuhan residents had said the January 20 surge in case notifications was a key day for the city's citizens to shift their attitude toward the epidemic. In rural Hubei Province, outside Wuhan, Jan. 23 was the "critical day" for many villagers to realize the severity of the epidemic. This Day, Wuhan Begins"close a city".

Also on this day, "China's rural population is large, health and medical conditions are relatively poor, farmers' awareness of prevention is weak, the mobility of migrant workers and businesses is strong, and management is difficult, " the People's Daily said in a commentary. It was the Spring Festival holiday, and a large number of migrant workers returned to the countryside from the cities. During the Spring Festival, most of the rural areas have activities such as visiting relatives and friends, Performing Arts and so on. The level of personnel gathering is high, and the situation of preventing new-type pneumonia is even more severe."

It often takes some time for the command of epidemic prevention and control to move from cities to towns and villages to villages. According to southern weekend reporter understanding, Hubei Township Epidemic Prevention and control work, the real start about January 23.

According to the director of the Public Health Department of the Town Hospital of Fengjiang's village, on the morning of January 22, the town held a meeting of the health system to train the village doctors of the administrative villages, and all the staff of the town hospital were recalled to work. In the afternoon of the same day, the town government also held a town-wide meeting of village cadres to re-emphasize the epidemic prevention and control work. On January 23, the head of the town hospital went to the county to participate in the emergency training of the county hospitals.

Feng Jiang also attended the town meeting, back to the village in the evening, they immediately began to count the village Wuhan Returnees. The statistics, including name, Sex, age, address, contact telephone, transportation to and from Wuhan, round-trip time and so on, are very detailed.

By then, the Spring Festival was approaching, and most people had already returned home in the Spring Festival rush. People returning from Wuhan have become the focus of attention.

Chen Chen, a university student in Wuhan, has been back in Pengdian Township, Xiaogan Dawu County, for 10 days since the village began counting people returning home from Wuhan on Jan. 22.

College students such as Chen Chen make up a certain proportion of the returning group in Wuhan. Wuhan has the largest number of university students in China, with 84 universities and colleges, with 138,000 graduate students and 969,000 college students, according to data at the end of 2018. In addition, the geographical advantage, millions of college students, Hubei Students are still many. And they returned home early in general, as early as Wuhan "key day" before January 20 has generally left.

Pengdian village party secretary in the evening of January 23 visit Chen Chen home, he did not wear a mask, with a notebook records, asked Chen Chen Chen home time, physical condition, Chen Chen Chen said nothing wrong, the village party secretary left. Didn't take his temperature. It was more based on trust.

Chen Chen told southern weekend by telephone that many people from the village had returned from Wuhan. "there are more cars with license plates in Hubei than in Xiaogan, " he said. His brother returned home the day before the blockade, while his sister returned only hours before.

These Wuhan returnees, have become the village doctors this Spring Festival "work object. ".

2
1:44

2

###1:44

Village Doctor Feng Jiang's "work object" is 44 people returning from Wuhan.

This is one of the administrative villages with the largest number of returnees from Wuhan in the town. Feng Jiang was a little nervous. "Once something goes wrong, our responsibility will be huge. " Not Commensurate with the huge pressure of the sudden epidemic prevention, he was the only doctor in the village, he couldn't find these 44 people every day to take their temperature.

"I can only tell the team leaders in the village to keep an eye on everyone's movements and tell them to stay at home and not run around, " Feng said.

In Hubei Township Epidemic Prevention and control, the villagers group leader is often the most front-line screening personnel. A town official in a town in Ezhou explained that team leaders knew what was going on in each household and were able to map the platoon.

Epidemic Prevention and control, uneven in different villages. In another village with fewer than 10 returnees from Wuhan, the notice from the village cadres was harsher. "At six or seven o'clock tomorrow morning, our village cadres will be patrolling the roads. If anyone is found not to be dissuaded, he will go his own way and pay new year's calls, don't blame US FOR BEING UNKIND! "

In addition to constantly telling villagers in the Wechat Group, "If you have fever recently, general weakness, respiratory symptoms such as dry cough or dyspnea, please feel free to see a doctor at any time, " and attach your mobile phone number, feng Jiang also repeated to the villagers the eight-sentence formula to prevent pneumonia: "Wash hands frequently, wear a mask, less parties, more ventilation, avoid game, eat cooked food, follow the doctor's advice, do not panic. "

"I think this eight-sentence formula is the best, " Feng said. "villagers can not understand and remember it too much. ".

In rural areas, advocacy needs to arrive in a more grounded manner. In some villages, staff members held horns, beat drums and gongs on the village road, and advertised in local dialects, content is often "ban all group worship activities, " "do not visit relatives and friends, " "do not exchange new year greetings, " "suggested SMS New Year, " "must wear a mask to go out.

A rural anti-epidemic video circulating on the Internet shows a village doctor spraying disinfectant in a fog-shrouded village with doors closed.

Instead of spraying disinfectant alone, Feng reports statistics to the Public Health Department of the town hospital by 12 noon each day. On January 23, he wrote the registration form by hand, but was told that it would not meet the requirements and that he would have to set up a unified electronic archive. Feng Jiang is not very familiar with the use of computers, had to ask the young people in the village, to help him register the statistical table on the computer, this just barely completed the report.

The village cadres did not rest either. In the village cadres' repeated reminders of the "untimely" situation in the village wechat group, finally, someone asked the village cadres in the group, "Is there anyone from Wuhan registered in our village? " One villager even asked for the list to be released.

An Old lady also expressed her concern in the group: There are two great-nephews coming back from Wuhan to visit, once a year, really do not want to be embarrassed to refuse, but also afraid. After much persuasion, the old lady finally refused.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The countryside in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture was as calm as it had always been during the Lunar New Year, when the news that the city had been closed to the public began to make people nervous. Photograph by Xiang Siqi

3
That you can't buy

3

###That you can't buy

Compared with the bustle of the village, the town 15 minutes away was deserted. Not many people come to see the doctor, medical staff frequently in and out, most wear disposable medical masks.

Village clinics can only prescribe medicines and look at the simplest diseases. Township level hospitals, in fact, become the first checkpoint for the township to deal with fever patients.

The pre-diagnosis and triage unit was also set up on January 23: those with normal body temperature went to the regular clinic, while those with high body temperature went to the fever clinic specially set up for this outbreak of pneumonia. The three-storey Inpatient Department has also opened up the third floor as an isolation observation ward. The isolation ward, however, is not yet in use.

At 3 p.m. on January 24, an elderly patient was given a disposable surgical mask after taking her temperature at the triage clinic. The thermometer showed 37.1 C and the doctor on duty recorded the relevant information, "temperature normal, go to the next room to see a doctor, " he said. The old man slouched away.

Next to a young man who had just taken his temperature, also came forward to ask for a mask, the doctor shook his head and said: "NO GOODS! " Some people questioned why the elderly can get a mask. The doctor explained: "Old Age, easy to get the disease (pneumonia) . "

This is the township epidemic prevention medical resources shortage of a cross-section.

Town hospital director of Public Health Department, January 23 statistics, from January 1, the town from Wuhan, more than 370 people returned home, 24 also increased, "estimated 300 to 400 people. ". Every day before 4:00 p.m. , she had to report the whole town back to the county.

The director said that the town hospital mask and other medical supplies are in short supply, "doctors and nurses are not enough to issue" , although reported to the County Center for Disease Control, but there is no material down. January 24 at 3:00 pm, the town hospital director from the county procurement supplies back, but did not collect enough masks, only a part of the county pharmacy bought a "colorful" non-medical masks.

A worrying detail is that, as of the night of January 24, none of the town's 17 administrative villages had masks for doctors who were in direct contact with Wuhan returnees. Feng said that in the wechat group that the village doctor contacted with the town hospital, several village doctors asked for a mask from the president: "We have to give each village doctor a right? " The president did not reply.

Feng Jiang told southern weekend that the training in the town hospital used courseware to talk about suspected symptoms, prevention and control measures, but did not issue any materials. He has no disinfectant, no mask, no mercury thermometer, just an infrared thermometer he bought on an e-commerce platform more than a year ago. "normally we don't have any of these in reserve at all, but now we're in desperate times, so there's no time. "

There are other potential risks in rural immunization.

Huanggang is the second city to close, and Chen is from a village in Macheng, Huanggang's caretaker city. On the morning of January 24, the 30th of the Lunar New Year, she got on the highway from downtown Macheng and prepared to return to her grandmother's house for the New Year. Outside the highway, she saw Macheng Red Cross men in White Hazmat suits checking every car entering downtown Macheng, but leaving the city and entering the village without going through any checks.

With the promotion of Feng Jiang's village, the true and false news of road closures in the city kept coming.

On the morning of the first day of the New Year, the village was silent where the firecrackers had not stopped the night before. Villagers have received New Year phone calls, and mutual exchange of the pneumonia epidemic and its impact on traffic: "highway closure, " "can provincial road still walk, " "shuttle bus still running? ".

Not long after, the village cadre family car came, in the muddy dirt road back and forth over ruts, the trunk of the Audio loop broadcast: "This year, we do not visit relatives and friends New Year dinner, we go home, waiting for the spring bloom. "

At the request of the interviewee, Feng Jiang and Chen Chen Chen are assumed names
